{{Class 1}}

<div class="container">
<div class="header-box">
<div class="text" style="font-family:Almendra Display; color:#314323; font-size:30px;">'''The Corridors'''</div>
</div>
<div class="main-box">
<div class="text" style="color:#314323; font-family:Yusei Magic; text-align:left; font-size:15px; letter-spacing:0.5px;"> <br>
{{Blurimage|file=Level106Corridors1.png|caption=<span style="font-family:Sankofa Display; font-size:20px">Congratulations</span>|align=right}} Entering '''Eden''' for the first time places wanderers in a marble corridor. On the right side, a repeating set of openings are affixed to the wall. Each of these openings are precisely 2.5 meters tall and 1.6 meters wide, and will repeat themselves every 3.3 meters. They open up to a party cloudy sky, with the clouds adorning a pink and white color, similar to the clouds seen at sunset. However, the sky remains blue, and there is no sun or natural light source to be found. 
<br>
The left wall does not have any holes, instead only comprised of the marble found in the level. The walls and ceiling in the corridor are made up of Arabescato Marble specifically, with it receiving a coat of aquamarine blue paint. The paint is from a supplier named "Tezo's Art Supplies", and buckets of the product, alongside paint rollers, can be found across the corridors. When applied on the walls, the paint appears to replace the walling with the same type, but now in that blue color. This change applies to any surface it interacts with.
<br><br>
The ground in the corridors is completely covered in plant life. The flowers in '''Eden''' are entirely consisting of Lilacs and Alliums, with their visual qualities being virtually indistinguishable from the same plants found in the Frontrooms. [[False Grass]] is incredibly common in this level, with smaller versions of the entity common in the corridors. These variants are not immediately dangerous if stepped on, with their bite force only strong enough to break skin. If killed, however, False Grass will produce a chemical with similar agents to Opium called "Purple Death". The substance enters through the bloodstream, and produces and intense euphoric rush similar to heroin.
<br><br>
Purple Death is highly addictive, and overuse can lead to catatonia and excessive hemorrhages if not counteracted quickly. Laxatives and other detoxifying chemicals have been proven to be effective against Purple Death, with a 97% survival rate. Without, the survival rate drops to 36%.
<br><br>
About an hour of travel through the corridors will open up into the main area of '''Eden'''.
</div>
</div>
</div>



<div class="container">
<div class="header-box">
<div class="text" style="font-family:Almendra Display; color:#314323; font-size:30px;">'''The Fields'''</div>
</div>
<div class="main-box">
<div class="text" style="color:#314323; font-family:Yusei Magic; text-align:left; font-size:15px; letter-spacing:0.5px;"> <br>
{{Blurimage|file=Level106Plains.png|caption=<span style="font-family:Sankofa Display; font-size:20px">Your new home</span>|align=right}}
After passing through the corridors, the world around them will open up to the fields. This section of the backrooms is a space truly seen as infinite, with continual land generation going out millions of kilometers every way. Many have seen new sections of land high up in the sky, though none have been able to reach it. This is assumed to also appear below the level too, with it going upward and downward forever. The Sun in '''Eden''' always sits due east, casting a sunrise light across the entire landscape permanently. Cloud altitude allows for all in '''Eden''' to freely interact with them.
<br><br>
The various hills and mountainous ranges give way to great bodies of water. These lakes blend into the clouds below them, and will continually cause rain onto the land below. Despite this, none of the bodies of water in the fields have changed volumes. Each one hosts its own sea life, most of which edible to those traveling through the level. Much of the fields are inhabited by various wildlife. Many of these are either endangered or extinct in the frontrooms, and are completely passive to wanderers.
<br><br>
Colonies in '''Eden''' have been entirely successful, with many spread out amongst the first 42 kilometer radius of the grand tree. The grand tree is greatly similar to the one found in the garden of Eden in the Bible. Its fruit has been told to provide great regeneration benefits, but does not function the same as the one in the biblical story. This tree sits alone, with a massive forest surrounding it. This forest is separated by 5 meters of grassland, in which the only life inside of it are plants. Other similar forests exist as well, and have served as a mostly endless supply of wood and resources for base management and housing. 
</div>
</div>
</div>



<div class="container">
<div class="header-box">
<div class="text" style="font-family:Sankofa Display; color:#314323; font-size:30px;">'''GOD IS HERE'''</div>
</div>
<div class="main-box">
<div class="text" style="color:#314323; font-family:Yusei Magic; text-align:left; font-size:15px; letter-spacing:0.5px;"> <br>
{{Entity Class|no=N/A|Hab=Heavenly Levels|Int=5|Dan=2}}

{{Blurimage|file=GODISHERE.png|caption=<span style="font-family:Almendra Display; font-size:20px; color:black">''He's arrived''</span>|align=right}}
The only entity in the fields of Eden is called God by many of the inhabitants. God is a humanoid standing at roughly 2.5 meters tall and starkly contrasts the landscape with its pitch black attire. Upon God's head is the crown of thorns, a headpiece of varying size and dimension. 
<br><br>
God regularly travels about '''Eden''' and has been seen interacting with the environment and other wanderers. The entity largely remains positive despite its foreboding attire, often sharing excitement with those who appear in the level. This is communicated via telepathically, and the actual use of a mouth has not been confirmed. God's arrival is announced by fast bells playing exactly 30 minutes before it appears, often leading to discomfort for those unaware with it. Despite God's positive reputation and behavior however, it does seem to impose some sort of rule system in the outposts that form in the level. While unspecified, the rules that God appears to uphold to wanderers matches the ones on the Ten Commandments. When asked about the rules, God responded telling the wanderer that "they already knew them". 
<br><br>
If God finds people who have broken the rules, it will initially act with soft reprimands. These may include apologizing, returning good, or informing people of their misdeeds. Continuous transgression turns to more serious consequences, but God still will allow the wanderer to stay in '''Eden'''. However, if a wanderer breaks all of the rules, when meeting with God, they will suddenly fall through the ground and be sent to a random level. These individuals will no longer be able to access enter '''Eden'''.
</div>
</div>
</div>



<div class="container">
<div class="header-box">
<div class="text" style="font-family:Almendra Display; color:#314323; font-size:30px;">'''The Passage'''</div>
</div>
<div class="main-box">
<div class="text" style="color:#314323; font-family:Yusei Magic; text-align:left; font-size:15px; letter-spacing:0.5px;"> <br>
'''Eden''', despite its other qualites, does contain a variety of entrances and exits. In all cases, if the wanderer has already walked through the corridors in '''Eden''', they will spawn in the fields rather than there. Additionally, only those who have "served god" will see these entrances. What serving god means is unknown.
<br><br>
<span style="font-family:Sankofa Display; font-size:20px;"> Entrances </span>
* White glowing doorways with replaces other doors across levels, stepping through these will provide passage into '''Eden'''.
* Angel statues and other angelic imagery ([[Level 941]]) may come to life and take wanderers to the level. Most cases the angel asks if the wanderer wants to leave before taking them.
* Noclipping through religious paintings in which deific figures are scribbled in black in [[Level 0.8]] sends one here.
* Riding a bicycle in [[Level 169]] leads one here.
<br><br>
<span style="font-family:Sankofa Display; font-size:20px;"> Exits </span>
* Disobeying all of God's rules will have the wanderer permanently kicked out of '''Eden''' and sent to a random level in the backrooms.
* However, asking God to leave will also send wanderers away. However, God will first ask where the wanderer wishes to go. 
* Some patches of the forests blend into [[Level 45]], causing those who enter to be sent there.
* Entering a sandy area may take the wanderer into [[Level 255]]. Do not believe in all paradises.
</div>
</div>
</div>



